"Wilhelm C., Bida J., Domin A., Hilse C., Kaiser B., Kesselmeier J., Lohr M., Müller A.M.","Interaction between global climate change and the physiological responses of algae",1997,"Photosynthetica","33","3-4",,"491","503",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0001474857&partnerID=40&md5=a00fa72987f18aead530543e6cbfe0b7","Universität Leipzig, Institut für Botanik, Johannisallee 21, D-04103 Leipzig, Germany; Max Planck-Institut für Chemie, Abteilung Biogeochemie, Postfach 3060, D-55020 Mainz, Germany","Wilhelm, C., Universität Leipzig, Institut für Botanik, Johannisallee 21, D-04103 Leipzig, Germany; Bida, J., Universität Leipzig, Institut für Botanik, Johannisallee 21, D-04103 Leipzig, Germany; Domin, A., Universität Leipzig, Institut für Botanik, Johannisallee 21, D-04103 Leipzig, Germany; Hilse, C., Universität Leipzig, Institut für Botanik, Johannisallee 21, D-04103 Leipzig, Germany; Kaiser, B., Universität Leipzig, Institut für Botanik, Johannisallee 21, D-04103 Leipzig, Germany; Kesselmeier, J., Max Planck-Institut für Chemie, Abteilung Biogeochemie, Postfach 3060, D-55020 Mainz, Germany; Lohr, M., Universität Leipzig, Institut für Botanik, Johannisallee 21, D-04103 Leipzig, Germany; Müller, A.M., Universität Leipzig, Institut für Botanik, Johannisallee 21, D-04103 Leipzig, Germany","The radiation climate as one essential factor influencing phytoplankton primary production will likely change in near future due to the increase of UV-A/B radiation and to stronger vertical mixing. The emission of dimethylsulphide (DMS) from dimethylsulphonium propionate (DMSP) influences the radiation climate due to its impact on cloud formation. The diatom Phaeodactylum tricornutum had a high acclimation ability to radiation stress resulting in a rapid recovery from stress induced losses in photosynthetic efficiency. In this case the primary production was not strongly impaired, and UV-B impaired photosynthesis by a mechanism different from that under excess PAR. The DMSP content of Prymnesium parvum was independent of irradiance and nitrogen supply. Total DMSP production of Prymnesium, however, was closely related to the age of the cells which was reduced under high irradiance.","α-tocopherol; Diadinoxanthin; Diatoxanthin; Dimethylsulphonium propionate; Phaeodactylum tricornutum; Photoinhibion; Photosynthesis; Phytoplankton; Prymnesium parvum; UV-B radiation",,,,,,,"Andreae, M.O., Climatic effects of changing atmospheric aerosol levels (1995) Future Climates of the World, pp. 341-392. , Henderson-Sellers, A. (ed.): Elsevier, Amsterdam; Blezinger, S., Wilhelm, C., Kesselmeier, J., Exchange of reduced sulphur compounds between marine phytoplankton and the ocean (1994) The Proceedings of EUROTRAC Symposium '94, pp. 559-562. , Borrel, P.M. (ed.): The Hague; Bold, H.C., The morphology of Chlamydomonas chlamydogoma sp. nov (1949) Bull. Torrey Bot. Club, 76, pp. 241-299; Büchel, C., Wilhelm, C., In vivo analysis of slow fluorescence induction kinetics in algae: Progress, problems and perspectives (1993) Photochem. Photobiol., 58, pp. 137-148; Charlson, R.J., Lovelock, J.E., Andreae, M.O., Warren, S.G., Oceanic phytoplankton, atmospheric sulphur, cloud albedo and climate (1987) Nature, 326, pp. 655-661; Crutzen, P.J., Ozone depletion: Ultraviolet on the increase (1992) Nature, 356, pp. 104-105; Cullen, J.J., Lesser, M.P., Inhibition of photosynthesis by ultraviolet radiation as a function of dose and dosage rate: Results from a marine diatom (1991) Mar. Biol., 111, pp. 182-190; Cullen, J.J., Neale, P.J., Ultraviolet radiation, ozone depletion and marine photosynthesis (1994) Photosynth. Res., 39, pp. 303-320; Demmig-Adams, B., Adams III, W.W., Heber, U., Neimanis, S., Winter, K., Krüger, A., Czygan, F.-C., Björkman, O., Inhibition of zeaxanthin formation and of rapid changes in radiationless energy dissipation by dithiothreitol in spinach leaves and chloroplasts (1990) Plant Physiol., 92, pp. 293-301; Döhler, G., Haas, F.T., UV effects on chlorophylls and carotenoids of the haptophyceaen alga Pavlova (1995) Photosynthetica, 31, pp. 157-160; Falkowski, P.G., Phytoplankton photosynthesis and global biochemical cycles (1994) Photosynth. Res., 39, pp. 235-258; Geel, C., Steendijk, M., Peeters, J.C.H., Snel, J.F.H., The use of chlorophyll fluorescence in the determination of photosynthetic capacity of phytoplankton (1995) Photosynthesis from Light to Biosphere., 5, pp. 885-888. , Mathis, P. (ed.): Kluwer Academic Publ., Dordrecht - Boston - London; Gröne, T., Kirst, G.A., The effect of nitrogen deficiency, methionine inhibitors of methionine metabolism on the DMSP contents of Tetraselmis subcordiformis (Stein) (1992) Mar. Biol., 112, pp. 497-503; Jeffrey, S.W., Humphrey, G.F., New spectrophotometric equations for determining chlorophylls a, b, c1 and c2 in higher plants, algae and natural phytoplankton (1975) Biochem. Physiol. Pflanzen, 167, pp. 191-194; Mantoura, R.F., Llewellyn, C.A., The rapid determination of algal chlorophyll and carotenoid pigments and their breakdown products in natural waters by reverse-phase high-performance liquid chromatography (1983) Anal. Chim. Acta, 151, pp. 297-314; Müller, D., Über jahres- Und lunarperiodische Erscheinungen bei einigen Braunalgen (1962) Bot. Mar., 4, pp. 140-155; Rajagopal, S., Murthy, D.S., Ultraviolet-B radiation induced alterations in photosynthetic electron transport activities of the cyanobacterium Synechococcus 6301 (1996) Photosynthetica, 32, pp. 281-284; Reed, R.H., Measurement and osmotic significance of β-dimethylsulphoniumpropionate in marine macroalgae (1983) Mar. Biol. Lett., 4, pp. 173-181; Sarmiento, J.L., Bender, M., Carbon biogeochemistry and climate change (1994) Photosynth. Res., 39, pp. 209-234; Sarmiento, J.L., Siegenthaler, U., New production and the Global Carbon Cycle (1992) Primary Productivity and Biogeochemical Cycles in the Sea., pp. 317-332. , Falkowski, P., Woodhead, A.D. (ed.): Plenum Press, New York; Turner, S.M., Malin, G., Liss, P., Harbow, D.S., Holligan, P.M., The seasonal variation of dimethyl sulfide and dimethylsulfoniopropionate concentrations in near-shore waters (1988) Limnol. Oceanogr., 33, pp. 364-375; White, R.H., Analysis of dimethyl sulfonium compounds in marine algae (1982) J. Mar. Res., 40, pp. 529-536; Wilhelm, C., Some critical remarks on the suitability of the concept of the photosynthetic unit in photosynthesis research and phytoplankton ecology (1993) Bot. Acta, 106, pp. 287-293; Wilhelm, C., Bida, J., Domin, A., Lohr, M., Is the measure of PSII quantum yield by means of in-vivo Chl a-fluorescence really a direct measure of phytoplankton primary production ? (1995) Photosynthesis: From Light to Biosphere, 5, pp. 809-812. , Mathis, P. (ed.): Kluwer Academic Publ., Dordrecht - Boston - London; Wilhelm, C., Lohr, M., Bida, J., Does photoinhibition really decrease primary production? (1996) Scientia Mar., 60, pp. 249-255","Wilhelm, C.; Universität Leipzig, Institut für Botanik, Johannisallee 21, D-04103 Leipzig, Germany; email: cwilhelm@rz.uni-leipzig.de",,,,,,,,03003604,,PHSYB,,"English","Photosynthetica",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-0001474857
